<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 8:50PM CST  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Marion
County through 915 PM CST...
At 849 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Detroit, or 13 miles west of Hamilton, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hamilton, Weston, Pigeye, Rankin Fite Airport, Byrd and Bexar.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
